void mmdb::set_new_float_unibin (  )

This call will produce correct floats in universal binaries but make them incompatible with old files. Without this call, float read/write will result in error after 6th digit. UniBin read/write of other types (realtype, shortreal, int etc) is not affected by this call, and to the best of knowledge is correct (no loss of precision).
